FBIS3-25471 "drafr035_a_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 February 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda CDR Members Take Hostages at Foreign Minstry EA2102215094 Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la Republique Rwandaise in French 1800 GMT 21 Feb 94 EA2102215094 Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la Republique Rwandaise Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] A demonstration by the Coalition for the Defense of the Republic [CDR] is being held in Kigali. At 1600, members of the Coalition for the Defense of the Republic sealed off the roundabout outside the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and hoisted their party's flag in front of the ministry. The CDR party wants to claim the seat reserved for it in the future National Assembly, as stipulated in the Arusha Peace Accord. As I speak to you, the demonstration is continuing and the personnel from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Cooperation, men and women, are being held hostage by the demonstrators.
